4:
P-please, forgive me! Don't do this! 
I beg you!
7:
Oh give me a break with all that
sniveling and blubbering! You knew
exactly what was going to happen
from the start!
9:
HAHAHA! Don't you worry, in just a
few moments, you'll be one of us.
14:
NO! NO!
KILL... KILL! MUST... KILL...
16:
Pull yourself together! This is just a...
special application of the curse.
You'll get used to it in time.
19:
Hmph... This one was no good either!
Whatever, get me the next subject!
21:
Yes, sir!
Bring the woman in, now!
27:
This one was caught harboring
humans. Given the unforgivable
nature of her crime, we feel she's a
prime candidate for this procedure.
34:
Hehehe! My, my, you're a REAL bad
one, aren't you, missus? You're just
what I need!
37:
O all-devouring Darkness, heed my
call! Upon our festering resentment
feed, and from this sinner's flesh
give birth to unfathomable power!
53:
You HAVE to be kidding me! Why
didn't you turn into a daemon?! The
transformation can't fail!
55:
You ARE a traitor, aren't you? You
betrayed our kind and saved those
filthy humans!
62:
Why the dejected look on your face?
As if on the verge of tears...
68:
Don't... come crying to me.
I'm not your mother.
71:
Lord Ilbis.
Enemy forces are approaching our
location!
73:
However... there has been a
development. It seems... Lord
Adjudicus stands at the head of the
enemy army.
75:
...Is that so? That miserable traitor. I
had a feeling he'd go and do
something like this.
77:
This woman is of no further use to
me. Feed her to the daemons, for all
I care.
80:
Then... Aha! The man from before.
Yes, yes, he'll make a PERFECT
daemon. Guards, bring the prisoner
to me at once!
83:
HAHAHA! Yes, someone cut from the
same cloth as me is precisely what I
need!
89:
One more hit should do it!
HEAVE!
92: I'll light the fuse! Everyone get back!
101:
Proceed exactly as we planned!
Deploy troops around the perimeter
of the Spire! Send an elite squadron
to the upper floors at once!
106:
It's imperative that we secure the
Lance before the Lord of Shadow
returns. I'll need your aid to do so.
109:
Lance? Would you mind sharing the
rest of your plan with us, Lord
Adjudicus?
112:
It's the central mechanism at the
core of the Spire. With it, one can
have full control over all Doomsday
Lances on the surface.
115:
From here on out, we'll be beset by
droves of daemons. I need to know
you'll do what's necessary when the
time comes.
120:
Alk... Even a moment's hesitation
could spell death. Do you
understand?
125:
I do. I...
I know what I need to do.

136:
Where the hell did this thing come
from?!
